<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="451" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1073,1530]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1073,1098]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body yellowish brown; scutum with two dark brown lateral patches; fifth palpal segment dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1109,1134]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1832,1854]" captionTargetBox="[186,1397,330,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[186,1398,330,1794]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Afrostilobezzia ornatithorax (Clastrier, 1988), female holotype: a—mouthparts; d—basisternum; c, d, e—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore (c), mid (d) and hind leg (e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233806/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,227,1110,1134]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Proboscis long and slender. Mandible armed with 
<number box="[817,831,1109,1134]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="6.0">6</number>
teeth (
<figureCitation box="[907,975,1109,1134]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1832,1854]" captionTargetBox="[186,1397,330,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[186,1398,330,1794]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Afrostilobezzia ornatithorax (Clastrier, 1988), female holotype: a—mouthparts; d—basisternum; c, d, e—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore (c), mid (d) and hind leg (e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233806/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">
Fig. 
<number box="[959,975,1110,1134]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Flagellum longer than wing, 
<quantity box="[1330,1431,1109,1134]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.61" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" unit="mm" value="1.61">1.61 mm</quantity>
, AR 
<number box="[198,251,1146,1170]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="0.99">0.99</number>
. Cervical sclerites not visible. Wing length 
<quantity box="[747,850,1145,1170]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.50 mm</quantity>
, CR 
<number box="[908,961,1146,1170]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="0.82">0.82</number>
. Some macrotrichia at wing apex present. Scutellum armed with 
<number box="[404,418,1182,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="4.0">4</number>
marginal setae. Basisternum relatively broad, arched, apices of lateral arms blunt (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1408,1181,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1832,1854]" captionTargetBox="[186,1397,330,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[186,1398,330,1794]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Afrostilobezzia ornatithorax (Clastrier, 1988), female holotype: a—mouthparts; d—basisternum; c, d, e—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore (c), mid (d) and hind leg (e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233806/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1408,1181,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Fore coxa with 
<number box="[325,341,1218,1242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="2.0">2</number>
, mid coxa with 
<number box="[519,533,1218,1242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="4.0">4</number>
and hind coxa with 
<number box="[761,775,1217,1242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="6.0">6</number>
setae. First tarsomere of fore leg with 
<number box="[1206,1248,1218,1242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
strong spines on proximal 
<number box="[259,270,1254,1278]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[281,296,1254,1278]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="3.0">3</number>
. Tarsomeres 
<number box="[443,485,1254,1278]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
of mid leg armed with 
<number box="[746,760,1254,1278]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="2.0">2</number>
distinct apical spines, additionally first tarsomere of mid leg with 
<number box="[207,221,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="1.0">1</number>
spine at 
<number box="[321,332,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[344,359,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="3.0">3</number>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[371,427,1289,1314]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial comb composed of 
<number box="[718,732,1290,1313]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="7.0">7</number>
spines, tibial spur short. Tarsomeres 
<number box="[1147,1189,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
of hind leg with three complete rows of palisade setae. Fourth tarsomere cordiform. Fifth tarsomere unmodified, armed with two slightly unequal and simple claws (
<figureCitation box="[452,524,1361,1386]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1832,1854]" captionTargetBox="[186,1397,330,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[186,1398,330,1794]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Afrostilobezzia ornatithorax (Clastrier, 1988), female holotype: a—mouthparts; d—basisternum; c, d, e—tarsomeres 4 and 5 of fore (c), mid (d) and hind leg (e)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233806/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">
Figs 
<number box="[509,524,1362,1386]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
c–e). 
<collectingCountry box="[585,621,1362,1385]" name="Chile" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">TR</collectingCountry>
(III) 
<number box="[680,718,1362,1386]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="2.3">2.3</number>
. Sternite 
<number box="[822,836,1362,1386]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="8.0">8</number>
with v-shaped caudomedian excavation, caudal lobes distinct (
<figureCitation box="[249,316,1397,1422]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,249,951,973]" captionTargetBox="[186,1394,193,934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[186,1394,193,934]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Afrostilobezzia ornatithorax (Clastrier, 1988), female holotype: a—distal abdominal segments, ventral view; b—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">
Fig. 
<number box="[301,316,1397,1422]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Seminal capsules ovoid, with well visible surface pores, unequal, with very short neck (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1399,1397,1422]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,249,951,973]" captionTargetBox="[186,1394,193,934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[186,1394,193,934]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Afrostilobezzia ornatithorax (Clastrier, 1988), female holotype: a—distal abdominal segments, ventral view; b—seminal capsules." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="451">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1399,1397,1422]" pageId="6" pageNumber="451" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
